n = 100
p = 50
sigma = matrix(NA, 50, 50)
for(i in 1:50){
  for(j in 1:50){
    sigma[i,j] = (0.7)^abs(i-j)
  }
}

theta = matrix(c(rep(10,2),rep(5,2), rep(1,9), rep(0, 50-13)),ncol = 1)
epsilon = matrix(rnorm(100),ncol = 1)
Xn = mvrnorm(n=100, mu=rep(0, 50), Sigma=sigma)
Yn = Xn%*%theta + epsilon

lasso3 = glmnet(X, Y, family = "gaussian", alpha = 1)

corrplot(cor(Xn[,1:5]))

ridge3 = glmnet(Xn, Yn, family = "gaussian", alpha = 0)
cvridge3 = cv.glmnet(Xn, Yn, type.measure="mse", alpha=0, family="gaussian")
